==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|byen|lang=enm}}, {{term|biggen|lang=enm}}, {{term|buggen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|bycgan|bycġan|to buy, pay for, acquire, redeem, ransom, procure, get done, sell|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*bugjaną||to buy}}, of uncertain origin. Perhaps from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*bhūgh-||to bend}}, or from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*bheugh-||to take away, deliver}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|by||to buy, purchase|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|osx|-}} {{term|buggian|lang=osx}}, {{term|buggean||to buy|lang=osx}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|byggja||to procure a wife, lend at interest, let out|lang=non}}, Gothic {{term|𐌱𐌿𐌲𐌾𐌰𐌽||tr=bugjan|lang=got|to buy|sc=Goth}}.

